# Editable config for scripts/mutants-bench.sh.
#
# The harness itself is frozen — to change the measured invocation, edit
# this file (and/or Cargo.toml / .cargo/mutants.toml / the Makefile) and
# commit. See docs/mutants-perf-learnings.md for the methodology.
#
# Note: the production mutation-testing invocation lives in the Makefile
# (rust-mutants* targets) with its optimizations already applied. This
# config file is a blank slate for future experimentation; leaving it
# empty exercises cargo-mutants in its vanilla configuration for an
# honest baseline.
#
# Supported knobs:
#   EXTRA_MUTANT_ARGS  — extra args appended to cargo mutants invocation
#   PRECOMPILE_CMD     — shell cmd run before each timed mutants invocation
#   IN_PLACE           — "1" (default) passes --in-place; "0" for copy mode
#
# Any other exports (RUSTC_WRAPPER, CARGO_TARGET_DIR, RUSTFLAGS, ...) are
# plain env vars that cargo will see.

EXTRA_MUTANT_ARGS=""
PRECOMPILE_CMD=""
